posts.com: I’m gonna keep this short and sweet: Caleb is kicking David's ass. Maybe this "new Plant" is a real thing, or perhaps he’ll keep being the elusive leaf in the wind we know him as. Regardless, the feet-of-stone Benavidez is losing come March. First off: Plant is arguably the most slick fight today, with Haney following second. He was only stopped by Canelo because of Canelo’s ability to cut the ring and pin slimy opponents down. Both traits Benavidez lacks. Coupled with the fact that Plant cannot stay on the ropes, even if a gun was held to his head, Benavidez has no chance. Against Dirrell, David struggled to deal with him, unless Dirrell decided to fight with him or stayed on the ropes for too long, BOTH things that will NEVER happen in the large ring Plant and David is fighting in. Next, I wanna move onto something a little less objective, and more speculative: Plant’s newfound tree-like power. Plant, before and after the Dirrell fight, testified that he’s rooting his feet down like an oak tree. That claim was backed by the nasty KO Plant fed Dirrell. After that, I have no choice but to believe Plant, and trust in his middleweight power. Consider this: David has been knocked down and hurt by a flimsy get-off-me left hook. Imagine David taking a serious, body-burying shovel hook similar to the one gifted to Dirrell. Do you think he’d get up? Especially after getting outboxed and taunted for 8 rounds straight? The answer is no. The glass chinned Benavidez CANNOT take a hook like that from Plant. In summary, we know that inorder to beat Plant, you need to be able to cut the ring well, pin the gliding leaf down, and hit hard AND in rapid volume. David has none of that. To beat DB, you need to be an elusive monster, not staying on the ropes for more than a microsecond. Alternatively, you can feed him a hard hook or two. Plant can do both. To believe Benavidez can defeat Plant is to believe Benavidez is on the same level as Canelo, but that is not the case.

DTM doesn't cost near as much for travel as IndyCar given it's 8 weekends and 6 of them are within a few hundred miles of each other, IMSA is also very high, NASCAR is extremely high. Just the drive to Long Beach and back from Indy is probably about as much mileage as the entire DTM season, that's one of the reasons why B-tier American series like MotoAmerica and SRO are so shit compared to their European equivalents.

The old testing rules had some big upfront costs to take full advantage of like a separate test team, and you know, Ferrari owning their own damn track. A lot of the teams were even literally across the road from Silverstone but then you had the Saubers and MInardis of the world that had to spend a lot more money to test somewhere. In season testing bans mostly go along with strict restrictions on number of engines and such, which are trying to clamp down the cost on the manufacturer end as much as the team end.

Also one other thing is that almost every other fighter would have panicked or lost focus at some point and so have gotten subbed. You can pretty clearly see hooker panic and take too long to respond after he gets taken down. Volk has a very rare composure because most fighters are shook by one of or a combination of the following: makachev's reputation of being good on the ground, makachev's top control and ease in transitioning/scrambling, the "bright lights of the octagon" and opportunity to beat makachev who is a top p4p fighter.

Dagis have also exploited the seemingly still prevalent myth stemming from early ufc that being on the bottom is somehow a dominant position. They know there are fighters who are content to lay of their back because of their bjj experience. There have been many, many fights in the modern era of mma where fighters could have tried to get up but were content to be on the bottom and try to look for subs and they have lost entire if not multiple rounds and didn't even realise how retarded their tactics were. In reality the best gameplan for the most part against a good wrestler is to treat the floor like lava and get up as soon as possible. Dagi and fence sub grappling is based around nullifying the required explosion/wall walking for this though, and so obviously more specific gameplanning is needed

I know out defense played like shit and our special team was atrocious. I know all of that but I’m still heartbroken and irrationally feel like we were robbed. I know bad calls are a part of every game but I been so emotionally wounded. That not why the Chiefs won but I just have so much emotions - anger and sadness and hatred. I yelled then stewed and I’ve just been crying for the last hour and a half. I don’t want to hate the chiefs or Patrick Mahomes or the refs. But I do. I can’t help but feel like things are biased toward PM. I hate them all with a burning passion that is exhausting. So much anger and sadness and hatred for fucking what? Chiefs are just people who love their team like we love our team. I started really watching the NFL and caring about football during the pandemic year. This Eagles team was the first team I really follow. I loved Jalen and Coach Sirianni. Then I learned about the team and fell in love with so many players on it. I listen to sports show all the time and spend so much time on the team. I follow every draft show and trade news and watch mic’up and listen to players’ podcasts. Following football has taught me a lot if lessons I never got to experience myself, but I’m done.

I will always love the Eagles, but I’m too weak to be a spectator and follower of sports. I am not on the team. I have no effect on the outcome of the game. The only thing I can do is sit and wait in front of the TV. Even when they win, I didn’t accomplish anything. It’s just a parasocial relationship and a poor investment of my time and emotional energy, which I barely have enough of for myself.
The PLAYERS can learn something from this experience, like Jalen said. But for me, there’s nothing a spectator like myself can really TRULY learn from it because I wasn’t there. I was just watching.

It’s time to put energy into MY life and on things I CAN control.

I just needed somewhere to write this message

Thanks Bird Gang. Fly Eagles Fly
